cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with camera relocalization, which is a task in computer vision and robotics. The proposed method uses uncertainty driven regression forests to jointly exploit points and lines in RGB-D images. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves robotics and machine learning techniques, which suggest that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses regression forests, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence, indicating that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves geometric information and spatial structures, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.GR (Graphics).
